3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX calculates funding rates every hour based on the premium between perpetual and index prices using 8-hour TWAP methodology. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per payment to prevent extreme scenarios. Payments occur precisely every hour, with rates determined by the 30-second TWAP of the premium/discount before each funding timestamp. Long positions pay when rates are positive, shorts pay when negative, creating predictable cash flows for arbitrageurs."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM's role as the hub token of the Cosmos ecosystem creates consistent funding rate premiums during IBC adoption phases and ecosystem growth. The pair benefits from dYdX's Cosmos-native infrastructure, reducing settlement friction compared to Ethereum-based competitors. ATOM's moderate volatility and strong institutional backing provide stable funding rate patterns ideal for systematic arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical ATOM Funding Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM funding rates on dYdX typically range from -0.01% to +0.05% hourly, with notable spikes during Cosmos ecosystem announcements and IBC developments. The migration to dYdX v4 has resulted in more stable funding rates due to improved market maker incentives and reduced MEV extraction. During major Cosmos upgrades like Gaia releases, ATOM funding rates have historically sustained positive premiums for 24-48 hours. The 1-hour interval creates more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour competitors, particularly beneficial during Cosmos-specific news cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategies and Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM funding arbitrage on dYdX benefits from the exchange's maker rebates and tight spreads, typically under 2 basis points during normal market conditions. Cross-exchange arbitrage with Binance and OKX ATOM perpetuals can capture 10-30 basis point differences during funding rate divergences. The hourly funding schedule allows for more frequent position adjustments and reduced overnight exposure risk. Delta-neutral strategies work particularly well during Cosmos ecosystem events when spot ATOM often trades at premiums to perpetual futures, creating systematic funding collection opportunities."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX v4's transition to Cosmos introduces validator set risks and potential network congestion during high-volume periods affecting trade execution. ATOM's correlation with broader Cosmos ecosystem tokens requires monitoring IBC flow disruptions that can impact funding rate stability. The exchange's insurance fund provides additional protection, but traders should monitor fund levels during volatile periods. Position sizing should account for dYdX's relatively lower volume compared to centralized exchanges, with careful attention to slippage on larger positions exceeding $50,000 USDT."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ATOM funding rates on dYdX v4?","answer":"ATOM funding rates on dYdX typically range from -0.01% to +0.05% per hour, with an average around +0.008% hourly. During Cosmos ecosystem developments, rates can spike to +0.1% hourly for short periods."},{"question":"How does dYdX's 1-hour funding interval compare to other exchanges?","answer":"dYdX's hourly funding provides 24 payment opportunities daily versus 3 on most exchanges with 8-hour intervals. This creates more granular arbitrage opportunities but requires more active position management and higher transaction frequency."},{"question":"What risks are specific to ATOM perpetuals on dYdX?","answer":"Primary risks include dYdX v4's Cosmos validator dependencies, potential IBC network congestion affecting settlements, and lower liquidity compared to centralized exchanges. ATOM's ecosystem correlation can also create unexpected volatility during Cosmos-wide events."},{"question":"Can I use ATOM as collateral on dYdX for funding arbitrage?","answer":"No, dYdX v4 only accepts USDC as collateral for margin trading. You must convert ATOM holdings to USDC before engaging in perpetual trading or funding rate arbitrage strategies on the platform."}]}]
